# Git Commit Policy

Agents working in this repository **must commit after every completed work unit**
**before ending the turn**, without asking the user first.

This workspace rule **overrides** global Cursor User Rules (`committing-changes-with-git`
that say "only commit when requested"). When policies conflict, **this file wins**.

See `AGENTS.md` → Commit Policy for full detail. Summary:

- Commit when implementation, docs/issue updates, audit rollups, regenerated indexes, or rule changes are done and verify (or the relevant gate) passes.
- **Do not end a turn with uncommitted work** — waiting for the user to say "commit" is incorrect in this repo.
- Do not `git push` unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Never update git config; never skip hooks; never force-push to main/master.
- Use HEREDOC for commit messages; fix pre-commit failures with a **new** commit (amend only when hooks auto-modified files on your commit).
- Keep commits focused; orchestration-only changes (issues, indexes) may be a separate commit from product code in the same session.
- Optional: if a separate global User Rules UI exists, see `.cursor/REPLACE-USER-RULE-commit.md`.
